ZCZC EE78
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 092300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY EVENING A LARGE AREA OF LOW PRESSURE IS EXP TO LIE ACROSS
NERN SCANDINAVIA AND THE NORWEGIAN BASIN WHILST A SMALLER AND SHALLOWER
LOW IS LIKELY TO LIE NEAR THE ISLES OF SCILLY. OVERNIGHT AND THROUGH THURSDAY
MORNING THE SCANDINAVIAN LOW DRIFTS FURTHER NE WHILE THE SMALL LOW IS EXP
TO MOV E THOUGH THE ENGLISH CHANNEL INTO THE NEAR CONTINENT AND FILL. THIS
ALLOWS THE AZORES HIGH TO EXTEND A RIDGE ACROSS THE S OF THE UK. MEANWHILE
ANOTHER LOW IS EXP TO FORM S OF ICELAND BY MIDDAY THURSDAY. THIS LOW THEN
MAKES SLOW EWARD PROGRESS ACROSS THE NORWEGIAN BASIN AND SCANDINAVIA FRIDAY
AND SATURDAY. MEANWHILE THE HIGH CELL DRIFTS NWARDS TO BECOME CENTRED OVER
THE UK FOR SATURDAY. STRG TO NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS INITIALLY POSS ACROSS
FASTNET LUNDY PLYMOUTH E SOLE NE FITZROY AND N BISCAY EASING WEDNESDAY
NIGHT. FURTHER STRG WINDS LIKELY ACROSS SHANNON AND S FITZROY THURSDAY AND
FRIDAY EASING FOR SATURDAY
NNNN